Description: Vencon Management, Inc. is a principal investment firm specializing in both private equity and venture capital. The firm typically invests
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Vencon Management, Inc. is a principal investment firm specializing in both private equity and venture capital. The firm typically invests in early stage, pre-commercialization to expansion stage companies. It also seeks to invest in leveraged buyouts, special situations, and spinouts with a special focus on spin-outs from corporations, universities, and the United States Government. The firm does not invest in pre-seed stages. It prefers to invest in alternative energy, nanotechnology, Green Technology, environmental technology including air, liquid, and solid pollution reduction technologies, biotechnology and pharmaceuticals, chemical manufacturing and processes, and silicon and gallium arsenide. In green technology the firm focuses on materials and gases for PV crystal, solar thermal and PV venture, fuel cells, boil fuels, hydrogen, water and water resources, biomaterials as bioplastics, and recycling of materials. The firm’s principal areas of interest regard dislocation of industries, undervalued companies, and platforming fragmented industries. It prefers to invest in companies based in the United States and may also consider investments in the Middle East (West Asia), Korea, Japan, and Russia. The firm typically invests between $500,000 and $3 million per transaction. It seeks to be a lead or co-investor and take a Board seat in its portfolio companies. The firm generally invests in the form of equity and debt instrument convertible into equity. It prefers to exit its investment between four and seven years through sale of the company, an initial public offering, or a repurchase of its ownership position by the portfolio company or another investor. Vencon Management, Inc. was founded in 1973 and is based in New York, New York.

Full Description: In December 1999, Pangea Systems became DoubleTwist, Inc. - a new application service provider (ASP)/ Internet company devoted to empowering life scientists. DoubleTwist.com integrates powerful tools and data behind automated research agents that retrieve and interpret data based on the user's scientific questions. The company's traditional data warehousing and mining software power the site, enabling life science research through an easy-to-use interface on the Web. DoubleTwist has established a talented and experienced development team of scientific and technical personnel dedicated to building software solutions that address the biological data management needs of life scientists. DoubleTwist's scientific team is comprised of leading experts in their respective fields of biochemistry, molecular biology, protein chemistry, bioinformatics, computer science and computational biology. They come to DoubleTwist from world-renowned institutions, including Stanford University, UCLA, UC Berkeley, UCSF, University of Pennsylvania, Sandoz Pharmaceutical, Onyx Pharmaceutical, Incyte, Molecular Simulations, Molecular Dynamics, Roche and Glaxo Wellcome. The company's software engineers have extensive experience in commercial-grade software systems, with particular expertise in relational database and object-oriented development. They come to DoubleTwist from some of the industry's most successful companies, including Apple, Oracle and IBM.

We’ll act fast and reach you within 30 minutes after your initial call to us.   Initially, it seems to be very easy to deal with the damage and clean up of the affected area, but in reality it’s different. Property restoration doesn’t only mean to remove the water, mold stains, odor or fire stains and smell; it’s much more. It’s about proper cleaning, drying, odor removal, decontamination, re-assessment and many other small and large level procedures. So don’t just trust anyone, hand over your property to safe and reliable hands like Water Damage San Francisco.   We provide you with a broad range of damage restoration services in California that are most frequently ordered by our clients: • Evaluation of Damage • Documentation of Damage through Paper, Video and Photographs • Cleanup and Debris Removal • Structural Drying and Water Extraction • Stain and Odor Removal • Sanitation • Air Quality Control and Air Scrubbing • Mold Testing and Mold Remediation • Fire, Smoke and Soot Cleanup Water Damage San Francisco offers all its smoke, fire, mold, flood and water damage services at reasonable prices. We never add extra fees to your final bill or to the pre-decided amount as we want our business to be neat, clean and free of unethical pricing. We value your time and money and that is why we offer you the freedom to know the price before we start the restoration process. If the restoration estimate suits your budget then we will move ahead and begin the restoring development.
